         <div type="translation">
            <ab>. . . fever with shivering; I adjure you, Michael, archangel of the earth, quotidian or nocturnal or [l. 5]  quartan, by the almighty Sabaoth, no longer fasten to the soul of the wearer (of this amulet) nor to his whole body.  I adjure you and the dead, deliver Taiolles, daughter of Isidoros, . . . [l. 10] "He who dwells in the help of the Highest will reside in the shelter of the God of heaven.  He will say to God you are my refuge and my helper, I put my trust in him."  "Our father who art in heaven, hallowed be thy will,  [l. 15] our daily bread."  "Holy holy Lord Sabaoth: heaven and earth are full of your holy glory."  Aniadaiia, Michael, the Lord of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, Eloei, Ele, [l. 20] Sabaoth, Oel.</ab>
         </div>
